---
The Catacombs of Nightfall are a Midgaard civic substructure under Ossuary Transport Court jurisdiction.
The Compact's shared registry and warrant system connected Nightfall to the Gloamvault and Dungeon Intake Yard through the same chain-of-custody architecture.
Municipal records categorize the complex under civic remainder: bodies where lineage claim, religious rite, and burial charter all failed to attach.
Ledgerhouse archives preserve intake manifests showing forest oath artifacts catalogued as civic remainder alongside condemned prisoner effects.
Midgaard treats the catacombs as a heritage site with unresolved liability: pre-Compact oaths were voided by civic processing, but descendants continue filing lineage claims.
The Reckoning Faction has sought deep register access for three generations; the complex is militarily secured and categorized as contested jurisdiction.
The Containment Office treats removing archive materials from Nightfall as a registry theft violation under Compact continuity law.

