---
Khenari ritual specialists classify the Catacombs of Nightfall as a corrupted death-rite site: civic registry treats the dead as administrative objects rather than participants in ongoing death-cycle relation.
Forest oath materials reclassified as civic remainder represent, in Khenari understanding, the multiply-dead: entities whose death-passage was voided by administrative act, leaving them bound to the procedural space of their reclassification.
This explains the oath-wraith population: spirits whose death-cycle was intercepted and converted into a civic file that was never properly closed.
Khenari death-rite practitioners report that standard passage rites do not function correctly in the catacombs — recognized by the oath-wraiths but treated as unadmissible petitions rather than ritual completion.
Proper closure would require both civic record correction and death-cycle completion for each affected spirit.
Khenari assessment: the catacombs require institutional reform, not simply ritual cleansing.

